Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

Because you could end up with changes from different sources that may be repetitive or wrong.

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?

Froks are made from repositories in github to github clone downloads repositories from github and branches are made within a same repository.

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?

It works as a backup that avoids losing track of changes inbetween plataforms